                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Capital punishment for man
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Sambalpur, May 21: A 54-year-old man was awarded capital punishment today for killing his granddaughter to offer blood to land goddess for better yield on the eve of Akshaya Tritiya last year.        
	On April 26 last year, Rajesh Hembram (54) of Badakundesara village under Jamankura police station area in Kuchinda, about 400km from here, sent his wife to a shop to bring wine and chana. Taking advantage of the situation, Rajesh killed his granddaughter Berenika Kandulana (9) with a sharp axe and collected blood in a bowl with an intention offer ing it the next day.        
	Driven by superstition that good crop was certain if the land goddess got blood, he did not hesitate to kill the hapless girl whose father died long back and mother deserted her after her second marriage.        
	Rajesh has been in Kuchinda sub-divisional jail since his arrest that day.         
	Kuchinda additional district judge Saroj Kumar Pati read out the judgment to Rajesh, whose condition is reportedly not well, as he has lost his mental balance.                                                                                                                                                           
